'''Nikolas "Nik" Berger''' (born March 18, 1974 in [[Salzburg]]) is an Austrian beach volleyball player.<ref>{{cite Sports-Reference |title=Nik Berger |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/be/nik-berger-1.html |accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref>

Berger began his career in indoor volleyball in 1986. Among his major achievements are the Austrian national championships runner-up with ''PLO/ASV Salzburg'' in 1992 and after he moved to the capital for playing with the club ''Donaukraft Vienna'', he was four times Austrian champion and Austrian Cup winner. At the [[1999 Men's European Volleyball Championship|1999 European Championship]], play at home in [[Vienna]], Berger finished his career in indoor volleyball.<ref>{{cite web |title=Berger/Doppler in nur zwei Jahren auf Europas Thron |url=http://www.news.at/articles/0335/20/63761_s3/berger-doppler-jahren-europas-thron |publisher=News.at |accessdate=1 May 2014 |language=German |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120904033535/http://www.news.at/articles/0335/20/63761_s3/berger-doppler-jahren-europas-thron |archivedate=4 September 2012 |df= }}</ref>

In 1993, he had also begun parallel career with the beach volleyball. With [[Oliver Stamm]], Berger competed at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]], in Sydney, but they lost to the Brazilian duo [[Zé Marco de Melo]]/[[Ricardo Santos (beach volleyball)|Ricardo Santos]].<ref>{{cite web |title=FIVB World Tour/Open XXVII Olympic Games September 16 – 26, 2000 (17) Nikolas Berger/Oliver Stamm, Austria |url=http://66.29.222.67/TeamPreview.aspx?TournID=783&ID1=574&ID2=550 |publisher=Beach Volleyball Database |accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref> At the [[2004 Summer Olympics]], in Athens, he plays with [[Florian Gosch]] after an injury to his season partner [[Clemens Doppler]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Austria Replaces Doppler with Gosch for Athens 2004 Beach Volleyball Competition |url=http://www.fivb.org/EN/BeachVolleyball/Competitions/olympics/math2004/PressRelease.asp?PRNo=1 |publisher=Fédération Internationale de Volleyball |accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref> A year earlier he won the [[2003 European Beach Volleyball Championships|European Championships]] with Doppler.<ref>{{cite web |title=Men's CEV € 100,000 European Championships August 27-31, 2003 Alanya, Turkey |url=http://www.bvbinfo.com/Tournament.asp?ID=1836 |publisher=Beach Volleyball Database |accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref>

After the 2005 season the duo Berger/Doppler went their separate ways.<ref>{{cite web |title=SWATCH-FIVB World Tour Idle, but Turkey Hosts Europeans |url=http://www.fivb.org/EN/BeachVolleyball/Competitions/WorldTour/2006/beach_page.asp?TRN=MSHA2006&PG=PRE&No=10129 |publisher=Fédération Internationale de Volleyball |accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref> Berger plays with [[Robert Nowotny]] until the 2008 season.

